## 10. Polish quality regression gate

Same shape as ┬¦9, different dimension: ┬¦9 prevents latency regressions shipping; ┬¦10 prevents quality regressions shipping.

**`scripts/eval/` is the single canonical polish eval harness family.** Two corpus scopes share one runner (`acceptance_gate.py`) + sibling (`overpolish-eval.py`):

- **Public** (tracked, ~100 synthetic cases): the CI gate. Runs on every polish PR. New features extend it.
- **Private** (gitignored, 1,590+ labeled founder dictations): manual deep runs. Never commit.

Never delete, truncate, or "start fresh" on either. Never build a parallel harness. Genuine issues get surgical edits, not recreation. Wholesale changes require founder approval.

**Swift Ōåö Python sync ŌĆö manual, not automated.** Swift polish logic lives in `Sources/EnviousWisprLLM/Prompting/` + `CustomWordsManager.swift`. Python mirror lives in `scripts/eval/acceptance_gate.py`. When Swift polish changes, update the mirror in the SAME PR and re-capture baseline via `--mode baseline --reason "..."`. Do NOT build auto-sync (Swift CLI dumper, shared text files, code generation). Decided 2026-04-18 on #299 after 5 Codex rounds on mirror drift: polish architecture is volatile (provider swaps, prompt rewrites), rigid auto-sync becomes a liability, not a safety net. Re-litigating requires founder approval + new evidence.

**Rule A ŌĆö polish-touching PRs run the smoke gate (advisory).** The `polish-eval-smoke` workflow fires automatically per the explicit allowlist in `polish-eval-smoke.yml:46-56`: `Sources/EnviousWisprLLM/**`, `Sources/EnviousWisprPipeline/LLMPolishStep.swift`, `Sources/EnviousWisprPostProcessing/CustomWordsManager.swift`, the named files `PolishMode.swift / PolishPlan.swift / PolishStyleConfig.swift / PromptEnvelope.swift / PromptBuildInput.swift`, `scripts/eval/**`, and the workflow file itself. `Sources/EnviousWisprCore/PromptVocabulary.swift` is NOT in the allowlist ŌĆö vocabulary changes do not trigger the gate. **Advisory only as of 2026-04-21** ŌĆö demoted from required after two blocker events in one night (Gemini 503, 20-min workflow timeout) eroded trust in the cloud-judge dependency. Still reports PASS/FAIL in PR UI; does not block merge. Read the result before merging polish changes. Locally validated polish work via `apple_runner` + 100-case corpus is the real signal now; see `afm-dual-mode-polish.md`. The companion `judge-drift-check` job was removed from CI entirely 2026-04-25 (run `python3 scripts/eval/acceptance_gate.py --mode meta-test --polish-model gpt-4o-mini` locally instead).

**Rule B ŌĆö new polish features extend the corpus in the same PR.** Shipping a new polish capability (emoji handling, list formatting, filler removal, any new behavior the prompt is asked to perform) is not complete until the feature PR also adds labeled corpus cases exercising that behavior, plus the updated baseline. One PR = feature code + test cases + baseline. Without this, the gate is blind to the new feature and can silently regress it on the next prompt change.

**Rule C ŌĆö baseline bumps require an explicit tag and founder approval.** If the eval legitimately needs a lower baseline (intentional quality trade), the PR description must include `BASELINE-BUMP:` with a one-line justification, and the founder must confirm the tradeoff before merge. Never bump the baseline to make a red check green without the tag.

**Why:** 2026-04-13 PR #272 (Gemma4 polish) shipped with clean unit tests and a real production regression. The cold-path rule (┬¦9) now catches the latency version of that pattern. The eval gate catches the quality version. Harness already exists (1,590 labeled transcripts, 5 categories, smoke/holdout/full splits); the #299 PR wires it into CI. Evals-as-code is the industry-standard defense against this exact failure class.

**How to apply:** Pathway-triggered knowledge file `.claude/knowledge/polish-eval.md` covers mechanics (corpus structure, adding cases, baseline-bump workflow, red-check debugging). Read it before touching `Sources/EnviousWisprLLM/`, `scripts/eval/`, or any polish prompt. Not loaded by default ŌĆö pathway-only ŌĆö to avoid bloating every session's context.

