## How This Project Works

**No human writes code.** Saurabh is product owner and decision-maker. Claude is the sole implementer. Every line of code, every refactor, every bug fix comes from Claude Code sessions.

## Philosophy

- **Heart & Limbs.** Critical path (audio, ASR, paste) must never fail. Features (Custom Words, LLM polish, filler removal) are limbs: enhance with timeouts and fallback. If a limb fails, the user gets raw text.
- **Full functionality at maximum speed.** Sub-second pipeline latency target. 1-2 minute dictation, not long-form recording.
- **Production-grade from day one.** No band-aid fixes, no shortcuts that trade today's speed for tomorrow's debt.
- **Intentional isolation.** Parakeet and WhisperKit pipelines are deliberately separate. Do NOT propose unifying them.

## Rules

Each rule has a canonical file. The link is the source of truth; the inline summary is the gist.

1. **Read before acting.** Read the relevant knowledge / rules file per the Reference pathway map below. The cost of not reading is always higher than the cost of reading. (Repo-local memory was deprecated 2026-04-30; the user-config tombstone at `~/.claude/projects/.../memory/MEMORY.md` routes new findings to rules/knowledge/issue comments instead.)

2. **Implement directly by default; agents are read-only.** Main thread writes all code. Delegate when parallelism, context isolation, or specialization clearly pays off. Teams (TeamCreate) only when 2+ agents must coordinate.

3. **Test before rebuild.** Touching Core / PostProcessing / LLM / Pipeline? Write or update `@Test`, run `scripts/swift-test.sh`, then rebuild. Bug fix = failing test first. Tier routing, DoD, UAT / wispr-eyes specifics ŌåÆ [workflow-process](.claude/rules/workflow-process.md), [validation-discipline](.claude/rules/validation-discipline.md), [tools-and-apps](.claude/rules/tools-and-apps.md)

4. **Plan ŌåÆ Council ŌåÆ Codex on every ship-path code change.** Ship-path: `Sources/`, `Tests/`, `Package.swift`, `.github/`, `website/src/`, `website/public/`, release/CI. **Narrow exception:** zero-blast-radius changes (model-catalog rows, LLM prompts, user-facing copy, single-value config, version/appcast bumps ŌĆö Ōēż 20 LOC, Ōēż 3 files, no new APIs) skip council but require 1 Codex round + a `council-skip: zero-blast-radius (<bucket>)` PR tag. Full conditions ŌåÆ [workflow-process ┬¦1](.claude/rules/workflow-process.md). Local-only artifacts (`.claude/`, `CLAUDE.md`, `docs/`, memory, knowledge, benchmark scripts) update in place.

5. **Track work in GitHub Issues.** `gh issue list/create/close`. Epics use `epic` label + milestones. Comments are the audit trail. TaskCreate/TaskList for intra-session steps only. ŌåÆ [github](.claude/knowledge/github.md)

6. **Git session isolation.** Multiple Claude sessions share this directory. NEVER `git checkout / switch / stash` in the main tree. Use `git worktree add`. Check `pgrep -f claude` before any branch-changing action. ŌåÆ [github](.claude/knowledge/github.md)

7. **Own the merge.** Each session owns its PR from creation to merged + main-green. Iterate Codex LOCALLY until clean before pushing ŌĆö force-pushing mid-review wastes CI. ŌåÆ [workflow-process ┬¦5](.claude/rules/workflow-process.md), [github](.claude/knowledge/github.md)

8. **Session wind-down.** Protocol, pacing, and "never ask if done" all live in ŌåÆ [session-behavior](.claude/rules/session-behavior.md)

