<!-- tier: 2 -->
# Pipeline Mechanics ŌĆö Runtime Behavior Reference

Why this exists: This explains how the recording and transcription pipeline actually behaves at runtime, not how it looks on paper. Skipping it leads to false assumptions about timing, streaming, and where bugs really live.

<!-- This file is CANONICAL. Describes how the pipeline actually behaves at runtime. -->

For type definitions and structural overview, see [architecture.md](architecture.md).

## 1. Parakeet Pipeline (Streaming or Batch)

User-selectable via `useStreamingASR` setting ("Live transcription" toggle). Default: batch (false) for cleaner raw output. When streaming is enabled, ASR runs DURING recording via `feedAudio()`. When batch, all ASR happens after stop.

### Timeline

```
PTT key-down
  |
  +- preWarmAudioInput()          [fire-and-forget Task]
  |   +- AudioCaptureManager.preWarm()  (BT codec switch)
  |
  +- startRecording()             [serialized Task via HotkeyService.recordingTask]
  |   +- ASRManager.startStreaming()
  |   +- Wire onBufferCaptured callback (RT thread -> MainActor -> feedAudio)
  |   +- startEnginePhase() (if not pre-warmed; reuses warm engine if available)
  |   |   +- prepare(): engine.start() + install tap + create PreRollForwarder
  |   +- waitForFormatStabilization (1.5s max, 200ms poll)
  |   +- beginCapturePhase():
  |   |   +- PreRollForwarder.activate() (two-step: drain pre-roll ring, commit to capturing)
  |   |   +- state = .recording
  |   +- startVADMonitoring()
  |
  +- [CONCURRENT] Audio tap fires every ~128ms (2048 frames @ 16kHz)
  |   +- Convert to 16kHz mono Float32
  |   +- Route through PreRollForwarder.route()
  |   +- In .capturing: forward to onSamples + onBufferCaptured + AsyncStream
  |   +- In .preRolling: store in ring buffer (500ms capacity)
  |
PTT key-up
  |
  +- requestStop() -> stopAndTranscribe()
  |   +- audioCapture.stopCapture() -> deactivateCapture() (engine stays warm)
  |   +- Schedule warm engine teardown (30s idle timeout)
  |   +- Deterministic drain barrier (wait for streaming buffers to be fed, 500ms max)
  |   +- Deactivate streaming forwarding
  |   +- LLMNetworkSession.preWarmIfConfigured() [fire-and-forget]
  |   +- VAD: filterSamples (remove silence segments)
  |   +- state = .transcribing
  |   +- if wasStreaming: transcribeWithStreamingRescue()
  |   |   +- try finalizeStreaming() -> ASRResult
  |   |   +- if empty/throws + VAD speech evidence: batch rescue via transcribe(audioSamples:)
  |   +- else: batch transcribe(audioSamples:) -> ASRResult
  |   +- state = .polishing (via onWillProcess callback)
  |   +- runTextProcessing() -> WordCorrection -> FillerRemoval -> LLMPolish
  |   +- Save transcript
  |   +- Paste cascade (4 tiers)
  |   +- state = .complete
```

### Key Facts

- `streamingASRActive` flag gates buffer delivery ŌĆö `deactivateStreamingForwarding()` sets it to false and nils `onBufferCaptured`.
- The `onBufferCaptured` callback runs on the **real-time audio thread**. `TapStoppedFlag` prevents it from allocating after teardown starts.
- `nonisolated(unsafe)` on the buffer is safe because it's created on the audio thread, transferred via Task, never accessed from both simultaneously.
- `defer { if !streamingSetupSucceeded { deactivateStreamingForwarding() } }` guarantees cleanup on all exit paths.
- `finalizeStreaming()` calls `SlidingWindowAsrManager.finish()` which flushes remaining audio and assembles text from per-chunk outputs with boundary-aware overlap removal.
- FluidAudio fork (saurabhav88/FluidAudio) uses fresh decoder state per chunk to prevent LSTM contamination that caused ~12% text loss. See [streaming-fix-2026-03-30.md](streaming-fix-2026-03-30.md) for full investigation.

### FluidAudio SlidingWindowAsrManager API Surface (v0.13.4 fork)

Full public API ŌĆö what we use vs what's available:

| Used | API | Notes |
|------|-----|-------|
| Yes | `SlidingWindowAsrManager(config:)` | Instantiated with `.streaming` preset |
| Yes | `start(models:)` | Called with pre-loaded AsrModels |
| Yes | `streamAudio(_ buffer:)` | Async. Our `feedAudio()` wraps this |
| Yes | `finish()` | Async throws. Returns final transcript string. Called in `finalizeStreaming()`. Uses chunk-aware text assembly (fork). |
| Yes | `cancel()` | Used in `cancelStreaming()` and `unload()` |
| No | `volatileTranscript` | Real-time in-progress hypothesis |
| No | `confirmedTranscript` | High-confidence committed text (requires `minContextForConfirmation: 10s`) |
| No | `transcriptionUpdates` | AsyncStream of `SlidingWindowTranscriptionUpdate` with confidence, token timings. Future: wire to overlay for live preview. |
| No | `reset()` | Re-use session across recordings |
| No | `configureVocabularyBoosting(vocabulary:ctcModels:config:)` | Per-chunk CTC rescoring. CTC evaluated (21+ runs), current production uses WordCorrector + LLM polish. CTC app wiring planned as ew-8a4.7 using FluidVoice dual-manager pattern (batch, not per-chunk). |

`SlidingWindowAsrConfig.streaming` preset: `chunkSeconds=11.0, hypothesisChunkSeconds=1.0, leftContextSeconds=2.0, rightContextSeconds=2.0, minContextForConfirmation=10.0, confirmationThreshold=0.80`. Do NOT change `rightContextSeconds` from 2.0 (decoder's 25-frame skip is hardcoded for this value; 4.0 caused catastrophic -93% text loss).

**Fork note:** saurabhav88/FluidAudio fork uses fresh `TdtDecoderState` per chunk in `transcribeChunk()` and chunk-aware text assembly in `finish()`. Without this fix, LSTM state contamination causes ~12% text loss at 60s+. See [streaming-fix-2026-03-30.md](streaming-fix-2026-03-30.md).

**Separate actor:** `StreamingEouAsrManager` exists for Parakeet EOU 120M (realtime model). Has `injectSilence()` and EOU callbacks. Not used -- the EOU model has no punctuation/capitalization.

### ASR Landscape

See [asr-landscape-2026.md](asr-landscape-2026.md) for model comparison, WER benchmarks, and evaluation status (bead ew-lomf).

### XPC Path (Default)

Both pipelines default to XPC-backed audio and ASR. The flow becomes:

```
Audio tap ŌåÆ AudioServiceHandler (XPC service process)
  ŌåÆ xpcSendQueue ŌåÆ NSXPCConnection ŌåÆ AudioCaptureProxy (host process)
  ŌåÆ onBufferCaptured ŌåÆ ASRManagerProxy ŌåÆ NSXPCConnection ŌåÆ ASRServiceHandler (XPC service process)
  ŌåÆ ParakeetBackend/WhisperKitBackend
```

XPC adds ~16KB Data serialization per buffer at ~39Hz on `xpcSendQueue` (not RT thread). Crash recovery: `interruptionHandler` fires ŌåÆ pipeline error state ŌåÆ next recording auto-relaunches service. Escape hatches: `defaults write com.enviouswispr.app useXPCAudioService -bool false` / `useXPCASRService -bool false`.

## 2. WhisperKit Batch Pipeline

WhisperKit does NOT stream ASR during recording. It records audio, then transcribes in a single batch after recording stops. An incremental background worker provides progressive results during recording.

### Timeline

```
PTT key-down
  |
  +- preWarmAudioInput()
  |   +- AudioCaptureManager.preWarm() (BT codec switch)
  |   +- Task { backend.prepare() } [defense-in-depth model load]
  |
  +- startRecording()
  |   +- state = .startingUp
  |   +- Check backend.isReady -> .loadingModel if needed
  |   +- startEnginePhase() / beginCapturePhase()
  |   +- state = .recording
  |   +- startVADMonitoring()
  |   +- startIncrementalWorker()
  |       +- WhisperKitIncrementalWorker: polls capturedSamples every ~3s
  |          Runs decode on accumulated audio, tracks coverage
  |          Uses full audio for <=30s, clipped (latest chunk) for >30s
  |
PTT key-up
  |
  +- requestStop() -> stopAndTranscribe()
  |   +- audioCapture.stopCapture() -> returns [Float]
  |   +- LLMNetworkSession.preWarmIfConfigured() [fire-and-forget]
  |   +- VAD: filterSamples
  |   +- state = .transcribing
  |   +- worker.finalize(finalSamples, speechSegments)
  |   |   +- Tail decode on unseen audio
  |   |   +- If worker result accepted -> use it
  |   |   +- If stale/empty -> full batch fallback via backend.transcribe()
  |   +- runTextProcessing() (same chain as Parakeet)
  |   +- Paste cascade
  |   +- state = .complete
  |   +- scheduleModelUnloadIfNeeded()
```

### Incremental Worker Details

- Runs as an independent actor, polls `audioSamplesProvider` closure every ~3 seconds.
- For audio <=30s: decodes full accumulated audio each cycle.
- For audio >30s: uses clipped strategy ŌĆö decodes only the latest chunk to avoid Whisper's 30s window hallucination.
- `finalize()` performs a tail decode on any samples the worker hasn't seen, then decides whether to accept the worker's result or fall back to a full batch decode.
- VAD chunking strategy (`chunkingStrategy: .vad`) is applied for audio >30s to prevent decoder hallucination.

### 9-State Machine

`WhisperKitPipelineState`: idle -> startingUp -> loadingModel -> ready -> recording -> transcribing -> polishing -> complete / error(String). Nine cases total ŌĆö the extra states (startingUp, loadingModel, ready) exist because WhisperKit has visible model loading latency that needs distinct overlay feedback, and error carries an associated message.

### Language Detection (LID) ŌĆö `meanProb` and `voteShare` are separate signals

`LanguageDetector` (multilingual v1, PR #257) emits two independent signals per detection. Do NOT collapse into a composite score.

- **`meanProb`** = average winning-language probability across windows (within-window confidence).
- **`voteShare`** = fraction of windows that picked the winning language (cross-window agreement).

WhisperKit's `detectLangauge` returns single-entry `langProbs` (argmax only, not a distribution) ŌĆö an earlier `softmaxFromLogProbs` impl always collapsed to `{lang: 1.0}`. Fix was majority-vote aggregation over multiple windows producing the two distinct signals.

Each signal gates a different decision:

- Single-shot switch bypass: `unanimous && meanProb >= 0.65` ŌĆö uses both.
- Session-prior rescue: gated on plurality (`voteShare`), NOT `meanProb`.
- Short-clip window dedupe: operates on window IDs, NOT scores.

A composite score hides the separate failure modes and breaks the bypass. Preserve both signals end-to-end. PR #257 UAT validated across 8 languages with confidence range 0.68ŌĆō1.00.

## 3. Paste Cascade

Both pipelines share the same 4-tier paste cascade. Target app and focused element are captured at **recording start** (not paste time), because LLM polishing can take seconds during which the user may switch apps.

### Tiers

| Tier | Method | Mechanism | Clipboard touched? | Focus change? |
|------|--------|-----------|-------------------|---------------|
| 1 | AX Direct | `kAXSelectedTextAttribute` on captured element | No | No |
| 2 | CGEvent Cmd+V | Activate app -> `CGEvent.post(.cgAnnotatedSessionEventTap)` | Yes | Yes |
| 2b | AppleScript | `click menu item "Paste" of menu "Edit" of menu bar 1` | Yes | Yes |
| 3 | Clipboard Only | `NSPasteboard.setString()` + user notification | Yes | No |

### Tier 1: AX Direct Insertion

- Validates element role against whitelist: `AXTextField`, `AXTextArea`, `AXComboBox`, `AXSearchField`.
- Checks `AXValue` is settable (not read-only).
- Snapshots `AXNumberOfCharacters` before and after ŌĆö verifies text actually appeared (Electron apps report success but don't render).
- AX timeout set to 1 second at capture time.
- If verification fails (count didn't increase, or counts unreadable), falls through to Tier 2.

### Tier 2: CGEvent Activation + Paste

- Calls `PasteService.forceActivateApp(pid:)` (AX `kAXFrontmostAttribute`) + `app.activate()`.
- Polls frontmost app at `activationPollIntervalMs` intervals until match or `activationTimeoutMs` (1 second total).
- Re-activates every 300ms in case first attempt was absorbed by the window server.
- On success: snapshot clipboard -> `pasteToActiveApp(text)` (set clipboard + dispatch Cmd+V) -> wait `clipboardRestoreDelayMs` -> restore clipboard (if enabled).

### Tier 2b: AppleScript Fallback

- Triggered when AX force-activate + CGEvent activation times out (app didn't come to front).
- One more AX force-activate attempt, then AppleScript: `tell application "System Events" tell (first process whose unix id is PID) click menu item "Paste" of menu "Edit" of menu bar 1`.
- Same clipboard snapshot/restore pattern.

### Tier 3: Clipboard Only

- Text is never lost ŌĆö if all active paste methods fail, text is placed on clipboard.
- Pipeline logs tier used for analytics.

### Clipboard Save/Restore

- `ClipboardSnapshot` captures all pasteboard items with all type representations (not just string).
- `changeCount` guard: before restoring, checks if current changeCount matches what we set. If a clipboard manager advanced it, restore is skipped to avoid clobbering their change.
- Restore delay: `clipboardRestoreDelayMs` gives the target app time to read the paste before we overwrite the clipboard.

## 4. Text Processing Chain

Post-ASR text goes through a sequential chain of `TextProcessingStep` conformers. Order matters.

### Step Order

```
ASR Text
  |
  +- 1. WordCorrectionStep (if enabled + custom words exist)
  |     Regex-based: matches ASR output against user's custom word list
  |     Fixes proper nouns, technical terms the ASR misspells
  |
  +- 2. FillerRemovalStep (if enabled)
  |     Regex: removes um, uh, hmm, mm, mhm, ah, er (case-insensitive)
  |     Collapses resulting double spaces, trims
  |
  +- 3. LLMPolishStep (if provider != .none)
        Provider selection: OpenAI, Gemini, Ollama, Apple Intelligence
        Short-circuit: transcripts <=3 words pass through verbatim
        Apple Intelligence: own path (appleIntelligenceInstructions + custom vocab).
          Uses polish(text:instructions:) directly. Does not go through PromptPlanner.
        All other providers: PromptPlanner path (added 2026-04-08, #154):
          1. Build PromptBuildInput (transcript, provider, model, styleConfig,
             appName, language, customWords, focusSnapshot)
          2. If ${transcript} placeholder: resolve before passing to planner
          3. DefaultPromptPlanner.plan(input:) returns PolishPlan (mode + envelope):
             - TranscriptAnalyzer routes to PolishMode (inline/message/structured)
             - PromptFamily selects builder: Gemini=plain-label, OpenAI=prose, Gemma=few-shot
             - Builder assembles provider-specific PromptEnvelope (system+user messages)
          4. polisher.polish(envelope:config:onToken:) sends to LLM
          5. validatePolishOutput() with mode-aware thresholds
        Streaming: onToken callback always wired (Gemini uses streamGenerateContent SSE)
        Extended thinking: Gemini thinkingBudget / OpenAI reasoningEffort (configurable)
        Temperature: 0 (hardcoded for polish)
```


